      "a_whole_splits_into_two_parts_the_sing": "💡 A whole splits into two parts. The Singapore Math curriculum (1980s) made this the cornerstone for early addition and subtraction. ",
      "once_a_student_fluently_sees_10_6_4_7_": "Once a student fluently sees 10 = 6 + 4 = 7 + 3 = 5 + 5, they can add and subtract with much less effort.",
      "the_make_ten_facts_are_the_gateway_to_": "The \"make-ten\" facts are the gateway to all later regrouping. Doubles facts (1+1, 2+2, ...) are usually learned earliest.",
